#------------------------VARIABLE OPEN DATE----------------------

# --- CONVERTIR A FORMATO FECHA ---
datos$Open.Date <- suppressWarnings(as.Date(datos$Open.Date, format = "%m/%d/%Y"))

# --- ELIMINAR NA ---
open_dates <- na.omit(datos$Open.Date)

# --- CÁLCULO DE CLASES (REGLA DE STURGES) ---
n <- length(open_dates)
k <- ceiling(1 + 3.3 * log10(n))
min_fecha <- min(open_dates)
max_fecha <- max(open_dates)

# --- CALCULAR AMPLITUD EN DÍAS ---
rango_dias <- as.numeric(difftime(max_fecha, min_fecha, units = "days"))
amplitud_dias <- ceiling(rango_dias / k)

# --- CREAR LÍMITES DE CLASES EN FECHAS ---
limites <- seq(min_fecha, by = paste(amplitud_dias, "days"), length.out = k + 1)

# --- CREAR DATAFRAME DE CLASES ---
clases <- tibble::tibble(
  Clase = 1:k,
  Limite_Inferior = limites[-length(limites)],
  Limite_Superior = limites[-1]
)

# --- MOSTRAR TABLA DE CLASES EN DT ---
DT::datatable(
  clases,
  options = list(
    pageLength = k,
    autoWidth = TRUE,
    scrollX = TRUE,
    columnDefs = list(
      list(className = 'dt-center', targets = "_all")
    ),
    initComplete = JS(
      "function(settings, json) {",
      "$(this.api().table().header()).css({",
      "  'background-color': 'darkblue',",
      "  'color': 'white',",
      "  'font-weight': 'bold',",
      "  'font-family': 'Segoe UI'",
      "});",
      "}"
    ),
    rowCallback = JS(
      "function(row, data, index) {",
      "$(row).css('font-family', 'Segoe UI');",
      "$(row).css({'font-weight': 'bold', 'background-color': '#f9f9f9'});",
      "$('td', row).css({'text-align': 'center', 'padding': '5px'});",
      "}"
    ),
    dom = 't'
  ),
  caption = htmltools::tags$caption(
    style = 'caption-side: top; text-align: center; font-size:18px; font-weight: bold; font-family: Segoe UI; padding: 10px;',
    paste0("📅 10.1 Clases de Fechas de Apertura (Open Date) usando la Regla de Sturges (", k, " clases)")
  ),
  class = 'stripe hover compact nowrap',
  rownames = FALSE
)
# --- ASIGNAR CLASE A CADA FECHA ---

# --- FRECUENCIA POR CLASE ---

# --- HISTOGRAMA 1: POR REGLA DE STURGES (CUANTIFICABLE) ---

# 1. Filtrar y transformar Open.Date desde datos base
Open.Date_sturges <- datos %>%
  mutate(Open.Date = suppressWarnings(as.Date(Open.Date, format = "%m/%d/%Y"))) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Open.Date)) %>%
  pull(Open.Date)

# 2. Aplicar regla de Sturges
n_sturges <- length(Open.Date_sturges)
k_sturges <- ceiling(1 + 3.3 * log10(n_sturges))

# 3. Calcular rango y amplitud de fechas
min_fecha <- min(Open.Date_sturges)
max_fecha <- max(Open.Date_sturges)
rango_dias <- as.numeric(difftime(max_fecha, min_fecha, units = "days"))
amplitud_dias <- ceiling(rango_dias / k_sturges)

# 4. Crear límites e intervalos
breaks_sturges <- seq(min_fecha, by = paste(amplitud_dias, "days"), length.out = k_sturges + 1)
intervalos <- cut(Open.Date_sturges, breaks = breaks_sturges, right = FALSE)

# 5. Tabla de frecuencias
frecuencia_clases_sturges <- data.frame(Clase = intervalos) %>%
  group_by(Clase) %>%
  summarise(Frecuencia = n())

# 6. Histograma 1
library(ggplot2)

ggplot(frecuencia_clases_sturges, aes(x = Clase, y = Frecuencia, fill = Frecuencia)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity", color = "black", width = 1) +
  geom_text(aes(label = Frecuencia), vjust = -0.5, size = 3.5) +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "skyblue", high = "darkblue") +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = seq(0, max(frecuencia_clases_sturges$Frecuencia, na.rm = TRUE) + 5000, by = 5000),
                     labels = scales::comma_format()) +
  labs(
    title = "10.1.1 Regla de Sturges",
    x = "Intervalos de Open.Date",
    y = "Frecuencia Absoluta"
  ) +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    panel.background = element_blank(),
    axis.line = element_line(color = "black")
  )

}

# --- BOXPLOT Open.Date - Identificación de Outliers ---

# Filtrar valores válidos
datos_validos <- datos %>% filter(!is.na(Open.Date))

# Calcular estadísticos y límites con fechas como numéricos para IQR
datos_validos_num <- datos_validos %>%
  mutate(Open.Date.num = as.numeric(Open.Date))

estadisticas <- datos_validos_num %>%
  summarise(
    xmin = min(Open.Date),
    q1 = as.Date(quantile(Open.Date.num, 0.25), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    q2 = as.Date(median(Open.Date.num), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    q3 = as.Date(quantile(Open.Date.num, 0.75), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    xmax = max(Open.Date)
  ) %>%
  mutate(
    iqr = as.numeric(q3 - q1),
    lower_fence = q1 - as.difftime(1.5 * iqr, units = "days"),
    upper_fence = q3 + as.difftime(1.5 * iqr, units = "days")
  )

# Extraer valores
xmin <- estadisticas$xmin
q1 <- estadisticas$q1
q2 <- estadisticas$q2
q3 <- estadisticas$q3
xmax <- estadisticas$xmax
lower_fence <- estadisticas$lower_fence
upper_fence <- estadisticas$upper_fence

# Identificar outliers
datos_outliers <- datos_validos %>%
  filter(Open.Date < lower_fence | Open.Date > upper_fence)

# DataFrame para cajas Q1–Q2 y Q2–Q3
cajas <- data.frame(
  xmin = c(q1, q2),
  xmax = c(q2, q3),
  fill = c(0.3, 0.8)
)

# Altura cajas
ymin_caja <- -0.02
ymax_caja <- 0.02

# Gráfico boxplot actualizado
ggplot() +
  # Cajas de los cuartiles
  geom_rect(
    data = cajas,
    aes(xmin = xmin, xmax = xmax, ymin = ymin_caja, ymax = ymax_caja, fill = fill),
    color = "black"
  ) +
  scale_fill_gradient(low = "skyblue", high = "darkblue") +
  
  # Bigotes (líneas horizontales)
  geom_segment(aes(x = lower_fence, xend = q1, y = 0, yend = 0), linewidth = 0.6) +
  geom_segment(aes(x = q3, xend = upper_fence, y = 0, yend = 0), linewidth = 0.6) +
  
  # Línea base eje X
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = "black", linewidth = 0.5) +
  
  # Líneas punteadas para límites y cuartiles
  geom_vline(
    xintercept = c(lower_fence, q1, q2, q3, upper_fence),
    linetype = "dotted",
    color = "darkblue",
    linewidth = 0.8
  ) +
  
  # Etiquetas
  annotate("text", x = lower_fence, y = -0.05, label = paste0("Lim. Inf\n", lower_fence), color = "blue", size = 4) +
  annotate("text", x = q1, y = -0.05, label = paste0("Q1\n", q1), color = "blue", size = 4) +
  annotate("text", x = q2, y = -0.05, label = paste0("Q2\n", q2), color = "blue", size = 4) +
  annotate("text", x = q3, y = -0.05, label = paste0("Q3\n", q3), color = "blue", size = 4) +
  annotate("text", x = upper_fence, y = -0.05, label = paste0("Lim. Sup\n", upper_fence), color = "blue", size = 4) +
  
  # Outliers en naranja con borde negro
  geom_point(
    data = datos_outliers,
    aes(x = Open.Date, y = 0),
    shape = 21,
    fill = "orange",
    color = "black",
    size = 2
  ) +
  
  # Estética general
  scale_x_date(name = "Open.Date", date_breaks = "2 years", date_labels = "%Y") +
  ggtitle("10.1.4 Identificación Outliers (Open.Date)") +
  theme(
    panel.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = NA),
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "white", colour = NA),
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    axis.title.y = element_blank(),
    axis.text.y = element_blank(),
    axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
    legend.position = "none",
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size = 18, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.x = element_text(color = "black")
  )

# --- OJIVA CRECIENTE Y DECRECIENTE: Open.Date ---

tabla_ojiva <- frecuencia_clases_sturges %>%
  mutate(
    fi = Frecuencia,
    Fi_c = cumsum(fi) / sum(fi),
    Fi_d = rev(cumsum(rev(fi))) / sum(fi),
    xi = as.Date(sub("\\[|\\)|\\]", "", gsub(",.*", "", as.character(Clase))), format = "%Y-%m-%d") + floor(amplitud_dias / 2)
  ) %>%
  select(xi, Fi_c, Fi_d) %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = c(Fi_c, Fi_d), names_to = "Tipo", values_to = "Frecuencia") %>%
  mutate(
    Tipo = factor(Tipo, levels = c("Fi_c", "Fi_d"), labels = c("Ojiva Creciente (Fi)", "Ojiva Decreciente (Fi)"))
  )

ggplot(tabla_ojiva, aes(x = xi, y = Frecuencia, color = Tipo, linetype = Tipo)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = Tipo), size = 1.2) +
  geom_point(size = 3) +
  geom_text(aes(label = format(xi, "%Y-%m-%d")), vjust = -1.2, size = 2.5, fontface = "bold") +
  scale_x_date(
    name = "Marca de clase (xi)",
    date_breaks = "1 year",
    date_labels = "%Y"
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    limits = c(0, 1),
    breaks = seq(0, 1, 0.1),
    labels = scales::percent_format(accuracy = 1)
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(
    "Ojiva Creciente (Fi)" = "skyblue",
    "Ojiva Decreciente (Fi)" = "darkblue"
  )) +
  labs(
    title = "10.1.5 Ojiva Creciente y Decreciente (Open.Date Cuantificable)",
    y = "Frecuencia acumulada (relativa)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +
  theme(
    panel.grid = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1, size = 9),
    plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, face = "bold"),
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.direction = "horizontal",
    legend.box.margin = margin(t = 10),
    legend.title = element_blank(),

  )

      State %in% c("NY", "NJ", "PA", "DE", "MD", "DC") ~ "Atlantico Medio",
      State %in% c("CT", "RI", "MA", "VT", "NH", "ME") ~ "Noreste",
      TRUE ~ "Otra"
    ))
}

# --- CREAR frecuencia_final CON Open.Date Y Zona ---
frecuencia_final <- datos %>%
  filter(!is.na(Zona) & !is.na(Open.Date))

# --- (OPCIONAL) SI NECESITAS EL CONTEO POR ZONA SEPARADO ---
frecuencia_por_zona <- frecuencia_final %>%
  group_by(Zona) %>%
  summarise(ni = n(), .groups = "drop")

# --- 1. Definir zonas válidas ---
zonas_validas <- unique(frecuencia_final$Zona)

# --- 2. Resumen estadístico por zona ---
resumen_estadistico_Open.Date <- frecuencia_final %>%
  filter(Zona %in% zonas_validas) %>%
  group_by(Zona) %>%
  summarise(
    Total_Observaciones = n(),
    Media               = as.Date(mean(as.numeric(Open.Date)), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Mediana             = as.Date(median(as.numeric(Open.Date)), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Desviacion_Estandar = sd(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Minimo              = min(Open.Date, na.rm = TRUE),
    Maximo              = max(Open.Date, na.rm = TRUE),
    Q1                  = as.Date(quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.25, na.rm = TRUE), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Q3                  = as.Date(quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.75, na.rm = TRUE), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    IQR                 = IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Curtosis            = kurtosis(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Asimetria           = skewness(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Moda                = names(sort(table(Open.Date), decreasing = TRUE))[1],
    Outliers            = sum(
      as.numeric(Open.Date) < (quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.25, na.rm = TRUE) - 1.5 * IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE)) |
        as.numeric(Open.Date) > (quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.75, na.rm = TRUE) + 1.5 * IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE)),
      na.rm = TRUE
    ),
    .groups = 'drop'
  )

# --- 3. Resumen total por zonas ---
resumen_total_Open.Date <- resumen_estadistico_Open.Date %>%
  summarise(
    Zonas_Total         = n(),
    Observaciones_Total = sum(Total_Observaciones, na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Media          = mean(as.numeric(Media), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Mediana        = mean(as.numeric(Mediana), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_SD             = mean(Desviacion_Estandar, na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Min            = mean(as.numeric(Minimo), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Max            = mean(as.numeric(Maximo), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Q1             = mean(as.numeric(Q1), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Q3             = mean(as.numeric(Q3), na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_IQR            = mean(IQR, na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Curtosis       = mean(Curtosis, na.rm = TRUE),
    Prom_Asimetria      = mean(Asimetria, na.rm = TRUE),
    Total_Outliers      = sum(Outliers, na.rm = TRUE),
    Modas_Distintas     = n_distinct(Moda)
  ) %>%
  mutate(across(starts_with("Prom_"), ~ as.Date(.x, origin = "1970-01-01")))

# --- 4. Resumen general (sin agrupar) ---
resumen_general_Open.Date <- frecuencia_final %>%
  summarise(
    Total_Observaciones = n(),
    Media               = as.Date(mean(as.numeric(Open.Date)), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Mediana             = as.Date(median(as.numeric(Open.Date)), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Desviacion_Estandar = sd(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Minimo              = min(Open.Date, na.rm = TRUE),
    Maximo              = max(Open.Date, na.rm = TRUE),
    Q1                  = as.Date(quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.25, na.rm = TRUE), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    Q3                  = as.Date(quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.75, na.rm = TRUE), origin = "1970-01-01"),
    IQR                 = IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Curtosis            = kurtosis(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Asimetria           = skewness(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE),
    Moda                = names(sort(table(Open.Date), decreasing = TRUE))[1],
    Outliers            = sum(
      as.numeric(Open.Date) < (quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.25, na.rm = TRUE) - 1.5 * IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE)) |
        as.numeric(Open.Date) > (quantile(as.numeric(Open.Date), 0.75, na.rm = TRUE) + 1.5 * IQR(as.numeric(Open.Date), na.rm = TRUE)),
      na.rm = TRUE
    )
  )

# --- 5. Mostrar tablas resumen ---
print(resumen_estadistico_Open.Date)
